  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Yellow Belt Eighth and Seventh Gup The color yellow represents the seed that is scattered over the ground, in the hopes that it will germinate and grow. The key to Yellow Belt is patience, as it takes time to grow roots and begin to sprout. This belt takes on the cardinal element of Earth, and is a time for seeking ground. Yellow Belt Curriculum Introduction Form (Terra Moto) One-Steps 1–3 Techniques High Yellow Belt Curriculum Form (Riverbed) One-Steps 4–6 Techniques Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
